Idea 0 focuses on syntactic constraints (e.g., dependency trees, POS tags) during latent adversarial perturbation. While elegant, syntactically constrained adversarial attacks have been explored in prior work, such as Cheng et al.'s "Robust Text Generation via Adversarial Training" and other grammar-aware perturbation methods that use parsers to guide substitutions or constrain search spaces. The integration of soft syntactic regularization into continuous optimization is an advancement, but it lies within an already active research trajectory.

